undefined’. Here  the  first  definition  creates  a  command  with  no  arguments,  and  the  second,  a
command with one required argument:
\newcommand{\student}{Ms~O’Leary}
\newcommand{\defref}[1]{Definition~\ref{#1}}
Use  the  first  as  inI highly recommend \student{} to you. The  second  has  a  variable
