Ellipses are the three dots (usually three) indicating that a pattern continues. \begin{array}{cccc}
a_{0,0}    &a_{0,1}   &a_{0,2} &\ldots \\
a_{1,0}    &\ddots                     \\
\vdots
\end{array}
LATEX provides these. \cdotsHorizontal ellipsis with the dots raised to the center of the line, as in. Used
as:\( a_0\cdot a_1\cdots a_{n-1} \). \ddotsDiagonal ellipsis,.... See the above array example for a usage. \ldots
\mathellipsis
